{"name":"Iron Allergy (Major or Minor)","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<p>There’s a lot of iron in Mechadia due to the influence of technology, but your adventurer’s biology hearkens back to the Fey Realm of Dreams and contact with any object made of iron gives him a rash at best, Wounds at worst. As a minor Hindrance you suffer a -2 to all rolls while he’s in contact with iron. As a major Hindrance you suffer the -2 penalty and take a Wound if his bare flesh touches iron for more than a second or two. If struck by an iron weapon your adventurer would not suffer an additional Wound, but if he picked up iron in his bare hand he would take a Wound.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SusZe9AezqB3XGJA"}
